A word about Orders
*******************

   There are nine basic types of goals. These can be used in various
combinations to create orders. At the end of the game your experience
money and Combat Points will be determined on how well you completed
the goal for your side. The criteria for each goal are:

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Kill Everything: @{ui} You get 100% if all mechs are dead or
     disabled. You get 0% if any mechs survive or escaped.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Scout/Patrol: @{ui} At least one mech must survive/escape to answer
     ALL questions for the report at the end. If your side escapes
     leaving enemy mechs in control of the field your success is the
     ratio of the number of surviving mech divided into the number that
     went at LEAST half across the screen (to the dividing line).

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Recover, Find/Recover or Convoy Object: @{ui} You fail if the
     object is destroyed or captured by the other side. If you get the
     object you a percentage based on how badly the object is damaged.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Destroy or Find/Destroy Object: @{ui} You get 100% if the object is
     destroyed.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Convoy Across: @{ui} Your success is measured by the number of
     mechs that successfully reach the opposite side.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Hold Position: @{ui} If at least half you all operational mechs
     have stayed in position (inside the circle) for the required time
     you are 100% successful (even if everyone dies after that).


@EndNode

