Internal Components
*******************

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Weapons (W): @{ui} Destroyed with any hit.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Ammo (A): @{ui} Destroyed with any hit. The ammo will blow up doing
     internal damage to the mech.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Arm and Leg Actuators (x): @{ui} Destroyed with any hit. Leg hits
     will require a Pilot Skill roll to keep from falling. The status
     of your arms and legs is given in the status display. The first
     number is the modifier to hit for weapons in the limb. The second
     number is a weighted actuator damage. If it is over 6 the limb is
     unusable.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Engine (E): @{ui} Each hit causes the engine to generate 5 points
     per second of extra heat. There is a chance on ANY hit that the
     fusion engine will blow up. The odds are very good by three hits
     and 100% by four hits.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Gyro (G): @{ui} A gyro hit adds 3 points to all Pilot Skill rolls.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Jump Jets Ports (P): @{ui} Destroyed with any hit. Each hit
     destroys that port and reduces your jump range one hex.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Life Support (L): @{ui} Any hit destroys the life support system
     for the mechs cockpit. The mech pilot will take one point of
     damage every 50 seconds that the heat is over 1500. If the heat is
     over 2500 he will take two points of damage.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Sensors (S): @{ui} The first hit on sensors add 2 points to all
     Gunnery Skill rolls to hit targets. A second hit destroys your
     sensors and you can not hit anything with your weapons. It is
     still possible to melee.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Cockpit (C): @{ui} Any hit in the cockpit kills the pilot. End of
     Game.


